---

### 2. `.gitignore`
Create a file named `.gitignore` in your **root directory** (the same level as your `backend` and `frontend` folders). This will keep your repository clean and secure.

```text
# Prerequisites
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.DS_Store

# Environments
.env
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
venv/
env/
.venv/
.env

# Databases
*.sqlite3
*.db

# Editor folders
.vscode/
.idea/